<span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubjond.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bjond</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 280<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/23/02 7:01:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1176.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Hmm, can you really ..</span><hr size=1> .. change dieties in EQ now?  BTW, yes it would be nice if you could, say, take 75% of your xp and skills and such and roll them into a new character.  Or simply change your class with some appropriate effort -- reset to level 1, but keep all skills except the ones the new class doesn't have. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umaladominus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maladominus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 31<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/23/02 7:32:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1176.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hmm, can you really ..</span><hr size=1> Regarding deities: <br><br>Whoa?? Since when can we change deities in EQ? I never knew that..... it would be great if we could, but I never heard of it. <br><br>Regarding classes:  <br><br>Savah, I think it's a good idea too.... but it's also a drastic kind of gameplay change that most likely will never be implemented by Verant in the current game engine. Maybe in EverQuest II this may be possible. <br><br>Doing this in the current EQ game engine is near impossible, because it will break a lot of things. For example you start out as a Paladin. Then later on you choose to be drawn to the Dark Side, you become a fallen Paladin and you switch to a Shadow Knight profession. OK, major faction problems. When you were a Paladin you screwed up and antagonized all sorts of SK-friendly factions. So when you start your new life as a SK, you suddenly find yourself as a Shadow Knight that is KOS in your own SK guildhouse because they still hate you for all the things you did while you were previously a Paladin? This is just one example of how things can go horribly wrong if Verant implemented this kind of feature into the game, and Verant will need to spend months and months reworking everything and fixing faction glitches and bugs just to make this work properly.  I doubt they have the inclination to do that. <br><br>Dont get me wrong.... I think your idea is good, I just don't have any illusions that Verant will welcome this idea. <br><br>By the way.... this is something that has been implemented ever since 2nd Edition Dungeons and Dragons. Class-switching has always been possible..... for a steep price in experience points like Bjond noted. <br><br>The upcoming online RPG NeverwinterNights will allow that, and will also allow multi-classing.  The game is based on 3rd Edition D&amp;D rules. A character can start off as a Ranger, for example.... and then later in life choose to become a Rogue instead. I know that alignment switching has always been possible in D&amp;D games.... it's all part of the role playing aspect. Perfect example is the renegade Drow Elf Drizzt D'Urdenn.... he starts out as any other evil Inky.... and eventually becomes a Lawful Good type hero.  blech!! <br><br>Anyways I babbled enough..... if you feel like changing, then do it.  Play the class that <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> makes you happy</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> ..... not the one that makes you feel trapped because of all the time you invested in it. <br><br>Always look forward to what you could be, don't look back to what held you up. <br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usavahfv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SavahFV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/23/02 7:48:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1176.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hmm, can you really ..</span><hr size=1> Ee! I forgot to add that this'll only work on FV... (Since FV *is* the only server where you can change your deity...) <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  I don't feel like editing any messages right now.<br><br>And I don't feel like answering right now. If I did, I'd do it in norwegian. (Bwahahaha... I love Norway.) <p>~Savah<BR>Ranger of Tunare<BR>Circle of Sisters</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubjond.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bjond</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 282<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/23/02 8:12:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1176.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Uh, how do you change your diety?</span><hr size=1> I thought you could only change your alignment on FV (subject to  race, class, and religion restrictions).  Changing dieties would be really nice! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usavahfv.showPublicProfile?l